---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Configuration" description="Customize lean-ctx behavior with lean-ctx.config.json.">
  <p>
    lean-ctx can be configured per-project using a <code>lean-ctx.config.json</code> file in the
    project root. All settings are optional — lean-ctx works with sensible defaults out of the box.
  </p>

  <h2>Configuration File</h2>
  <pre><code>{`{
  "ignore": [
    "node_modules",
    ".git",
    "dist",
    "build",
    ".svelte-kit",
    "__pycache__",
    ".next"
  ],
  "compress": {
    "removeEmptyLines": true,
    "removeRedundantComments": true,
    "maxFileLines": 500
  },
  "patterns": {
    "npm": true,
    "git": true,
    "docker": true,
    "typescript": true
  }
}`}</code></pre>

  <h2>Options</h2>

  <h3>ignore</h3>
  <p>
    Array of directory and file names to exclude from <code>ctx_tree</code> and file operations.
    These are matched against path segments, not glob patterns.
  </p>

  <h3>compress</h3>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Option</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>removeEmptyLines</code></td><td><code>true</code></td><td>Strip empty lines from file reads</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>removeRedundantComments</code></td><td><code>true</code></td><td>Strip obvious comments (e.g. "// Import the module")</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>maxFileLines</code></td><td><code>500</code></td><td>Truncate files beyond this limit with a summary</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h3>patterns</h3>
  <p>
    Enable or disable specific shell output compression patterns. Set to <code>false</code> to
    disable compression for a specific tool's output.
  </p>

  <h2>Environment Variables</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Variable</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>LEAN_CTX_ROOT</code></td><td>Project root directory (set in editor MCP config)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>LEAN_CTX_PORT</code></td><td>Dashboard port (default: 3333)</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Creating the Config</h2>
  <p>
    The easiest way to create the config file is with the CLI:
  </p>
  <pre><code>lean-ctx init /path/to/project</code></pre>
  <p>
    This creates <code>lean-ctx.config.json</code> with sensible defaults, plus the editor config
    files for Cursor and Copilot.
  </p>
</DocsLayout>
